## 2. Universal acceptance criteria (every PR)

These must ALL be satisfied before a PR can be marked "ready to merge". A PR that
fails any of these is **blocked** regardless of other merits.

### 2.1 Non-negotiable rules (AGENTS.md §2) — instant blockers

- [ ] **1delta boundary**: 1delta API used for data/routing only — never in the
  custody or execution path. No vault code calls 1delta URLs or executes
  1delta-returned calldata directly.
- [ ] **Guardrails**: LLM can only tighten risk, never loosen. On-chain guardrails
  are the final backstop. Shared constants between `Guardrails.sol` and the TS
  validator come from `packages/shared`.
- [ ] **No AI-washing**: deterministic paths (yield math, peg deviation, oracle
  staleness, liquidity sizing, execution) remain deterministic. LLM is only used
  for unstructured→structured signal, rationale, novel events, UX.
- [ ] **Mantle-only**: no cross-chain execution. Chain ID hard-coded as `5000` where
  relevant.
- [ ] **Custody safety**: USDC-only deposit; USDY/AUSD via DEX with on-chain
  `minOut`; no KYC mint; no leverage; kill switch present on fund-moving contracts.
- [ ] **No secrets committed**: no private keys, RPC URLs, API keys, or wallet
  addresses in any committed file. `.env` is git-ignored.
- [ ] **Addresses verified**: every new protocol address has a `provenance` comment
  and has been confirmed via `extcodesize > 0` on a live or forked Mantle node.
  `null` entries in `addresses.ts` are acceptable only before the Phase 0.3 gate.
- [ ] **Scope discipline**: PR covers only the ROADMAP tasks listed in its title.
  No speculative features, no premature abstractions.

### 2.2 Code quality — blockers

- [ ] TypeScript strict mode passes with zero errors.
- [ ] ESLint passes with zero warnings.
- [ ] Solidity compiles with zero errors (warnings documented if unavoidable).
- [ ] No `console.log` / `console2.log` left in production (non-test) code.
- [ ] No commented-out code blocks ("explaining the change" comments).
- [ ] Money math uses `bigint`/fixed-point — no floats for on-chain amounts.
- [ ] All public/external Solidity functions have NatSpec (`@notice`, `@param`,
  `@return`).
- [ ] Fund-moving Solidity functions use checks-effects-interactions and have
  reentrancy guards (`ReentrancyGuard` or equivalent).
- [ ] No `address(0)` as a valid value for contract addresses passed in by callers.
- [ ] Custom errors used (not `require("string")`).

### 2.3 Tests — blockers

- [ ] Every new fund-moving contract path has a Forge test (happy path + guardrail
  violation + relevant edge cases).
- [ ] Every new agent/risk-engine path has a Vitest test.
- [ ] Fork tests assert on-chain state, not just that the call didn't revert.
- [ ] No test silently skips assertions (no empty `it()`, no `expect(true).toBe(true)`).

### 2.4 Documentation — blockers

- [ ] ROADMAP.md tasks covered by this PR are marked `[x] DONE` with a PR link.
- [ ] `packages/shared/addresses.ts` updated if any address was resolved/verified.
- [ ] `.env.example` updated if any new env var was introduced.
- [ ] If `SPEC.md`/`PLAN.md` assumptions changed, those files are updated in the
  same PR.

