## 3. Phase-specific acceptance criteria

### Phase 0 — Foundations & gates

- [ ] `forge build --offline` passes (solc pre-installed or static binary used).
- [ ] `forge test --no-match-contract ForkTest` passes offline.
- [ ] Fork tests (`ForkTest`) pass against a live Mantle fork.
- [ ] Task 0.3: `PROTOCOLS` nulls in `addresses.ts` filled in with verified addresses
  and `// verified @ block N` comments.
- [ ] Task 0.4: slippage table logged; explicit GO or AUSD-fallback decision recorded
  in ROADMAP.
- [ ] Task 0.6: `DemoTrigger` tests pass; `injectDepeg` + `clearDepeg` round-trip
  verified.
- [ ] All 7 scaffold gate checks pass.

### Phase 1 — Vault core

- [ ] `YieldVault` is ERC-4626 compliant (deposit/mint/withdraw/redeem).
- [ ] `Guardrails` constants imported from `packages/shared` — not hardcoded.
- [ ] `ADMIN`, `ALLOCATOR`, `GUARDIAN` roles present; unauthorized calls revert.
- [ ] Kill switch pauses deposits and rebalances; emergency withdraw still works.
- [ ] `AaveV3Adapter` does not hold funds — vault only.
- [ ] Forge tests: happy deposit→supply→withdraw; unauthorized rebalance reverts;
  pause blocks deposit.

### Phase 2 — RWA + risk guard

- [ ] `UsdyAdapter` enforces `minOut` on-chain and handles USDY blocklist revert.
- [ ] Depeg guard reads `RWADynamicOracle.getPrice()` — not a mock in production.
- [ ] `Decision` event emitted with `evidenceHash` (IPFS CID or `bytes32(0)` if not
  yet pinned) on every rebalance.
- [ ] `AgentBenchmark` records passive-USDY baseline correctly (share price at
  rebalance time vs USDY NAV).
- [ ] Forge tests: depeg fires de-risk; oracle staleness fires de-risk; normal state
  does not trigger de-risk.

### Phase 3 — Agent

- [ ] `LLMClient` interface is mockable; real implementation wraps `@anthropic-ai/sdk`
  only — no other LLM provider.
- [ ] Risk signal schema matches `SPEC.md` §3 exactly.
- [ ] TS guardrail validator rejects any allocation that violates `SPEC.md` §1 limits
  before signing.
- [ ] LLM rationale stored in agent DB and referenced in the `Decision` event
  `evidenceHash`.
- [ ] Scheduler tests cover: periodic tick, depeg event trigger, oracle-staleness
  trigger.

### Phase 4 — Frontend + ERC-8004

- [ ] ERC-8004 registration uses on-chain singletons if present (codesize > 0 at the
  0x8004 addresses); otherwise uses the minimal own registry deployed in Phase 3.
- [ ] UI follows `UI.md` — sentinel-light / sentinel-dark themes; purple accent;
  no inline styles overriding theme tokens.
- [ ] Account dashboard shows: balance, blended APY, bucket allocation, share price.
- [ ] Risk-guardian feed shows: each decision, AI rationale, evidence link.
- [ ] Baseline counter shows: passive USDY holder delta vs Sentinel delta in bps.
- [ ] Deposit/withdraw flow: gas estimate shown; tx hash shown on submit.
- [ ] Accessibility: interactive elements keyboard-focusable; no color-only
  information encoding.

### Phase 5 — Deploy

- [ ] All contracts verified on Mantlescan.
- [ ] `DEPLOYER_PRIVATE_KEY` used only for deploy; `ALLOCATOR_PRIVATE_KEY` is the
  hot operational key.
- [ ] Deployment addresses recorded in `packages/shared/addresses.ts` with
  `// deployed @ tx <hash>` provenance.
- [ ] Public demo endpoint live and smoke-tested.

