## 4. Review output format

Return a structured verdict:

```
## PR Review

**Verdict:** APPROVED | CHANGES REQUESTED | BLOCKED

### Blockers (must fix before merge)
- <item> — <file>:<line> — <reason>

### Required changes (non-blocking but must fix in this PR)
- <item>

### Suggestions (optional improvements)
- <item>

### Gate status
- [ ] TS typecheck
- [ ] TS lint
- [ ] TS test
- [ ] TS build
- [ ] Solidity build
- [ ] Solidity unit tests (offline)
- [ ] Fork tests (if applicable)
- [ ] ROADMAP tasks marked [x] DONE
- [ ] addresses.ts updated (if applicable)
- [ ] .env.example updated (if applicable)

### Notes
<anything else worth flagging>
```

A verdict of **BLOCKED** means a non-negotiable rule (AGENTS.md §2) was violated.
A verdict of **CHANGES REQUESTED** means a gate or code-quality check failed.
A verdict of **APPROVED** means all applicable checks in sections 2 and 3 pass.
```
